## 🐛 Bug Report

Named range defined in excel in format like worksheet!$1:$10 is removed when reading the file.

Lib version: 3.8.1

## Steps To Reproduce

const {Workbook} = require('../../lib/exceljs.nodejs');

const filenameIn = './NamedRangeIn.xlsx';
const filenameOut = './NamedRangeOut.xlsx';
const wb = new Workbook();
wb.xlsx
    .readFile(filenameIn)
    .then(() => wb.xlsx.writeFile(filenameOut))
    .then(() => {
        console.log('Done.');
    })
    .catch(error => {
        console.error('Error', error.stack);
    });

Open output file: NamedRangeOut.xlsx
Go to 'Formulas', open 'Name Manager'. See that there's no range named: RangeTest.

Looks like only ranges like [row][col]:[row][col] are valid.

[NamedRangeIn.xlsx](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/files/4374749/NamedRangeIn.xlsx)
[NamedRangeOut.xlsx](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/files/4374750/NamedRangeOut.xlsx)
[named_range_test.js.txt](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/files/4374751/named_range_test.js.txt)

