I read the exceljs source code, but I didn't find the code to handle 'Name Manager', exceljs may not currently support it.. 

```javascript
  // app-heading-pairs-xform.js

  render(xmlStream, model) {
    xmlStream.openNode('HeadingPairs');
    xmlStream.openNode('vt:vector', {size: 2, baseType: 'variant'});

    xmlStream.openNode('vt:variant');
    xmlStream.leafNode('vt:lpstr', undefined, 'Worksheets');
    xmlStream.closeNode();

    xmlStream.openNode('vt:variant');
    xmlStream.leafNode('vt:i4', undefined, model.length);
    xmlStream.closeNode();

    xmlStream.closeNode();
    xmlStream.closeNode();
  }

```

```xml
// app.xml

<HeadingPairs>
    <vt:vector size="4" baseType="variant">
      <vt:variant>
        <vt:lpstr>Worksheets</vt:lpstr>
      </vt:variant>
      <vt:variant>
        <vt:i4>2</vt:i4>
      </vt:variant>
      <vt:variant>
        <vt:lpstr>Named Ranges</vt:lpstr>
      </vt:variant>
      <vt:variant>
        <vt:i4>1</vt:i4>
      </vt:variant>
    </vt:vector>
  </HeadingPairs>
````

The lib supports named ranges, you can see them if you run the following code:
```javascript
    const tWorkbook = new Excel.Workbook();
    await tWorkbook.xlsx.read(fStream);
    console.log(tWorkbook.definedNames);
```
But I can confirm that at least named rows are not got parsed correctly. So a name assigned to a row in the 'Name Manager' looks like:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67019510/84869353-eb9a1180-b04b-11ea-8242-abc213f6c7ab.png)

When the `definedNames` go to console the named row is there, but it is not available in `definedNames.forEach` and disappear after saving:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67019510/84869272-cf967000-b04b-11ea-88fb-2c8f4f8186bf.png)
